1
00:00:46,921 --> 00:00:50,008
{\an8}The best agent in the agency,
Special Agent Alex.

2
00:00:50,091 --> 00:00:54,971
{\an8}She figured out the whereabouts
of Mikoy and Chiara Valtrovi.

3
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:59,350
{\an8}So you think Agent Alex will find Mikoy?

4
00:00:59,434 --> 00:01:01,061
{\an8}I think that's possible.

5
00:01:01,144 --> 00:01:03,396
{\an8}<i>Right at this moment,</i>
<i>the two of them are already in custody.</i>

6
00:01:59,327 --> 00:02:01,204
{\an8}I have a strong feeling they're okay.

7
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:02,831
{\an8}Very much alive.

8
00:02:50,378 --> 00:02:53,089
{\an8}And when you're young,
you're so in love, like,

9
00:02:53,172 --> 00:02:55,383
{\an8}crazy in love, like Beyoncé!

10
00:03:04,100 --> 00:03:05,393
{\an8}La Morte Bianca.

11
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:30,872
Ouch!

12
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:41,632
Hello? Anybody home?

13
00:05:45,178 --> 00:05:46,345
Anybody home?

14
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:49,265
Hey, have mercy on me!

15
00:05:49,849 --> 00:05:51,559
Let me out of here!

16
00:05:53,853 --> 00:05:56,647
Wait. Mikoy, relax, okay?

17
00:05:57,565 --> 00:05:59,609
Relax. Breathe.

18
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:06,866
That's it. Just relax. Breathe.

19
00:06:10,453 --> 00:06:11,579
Wait.

20
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:13,122
I've seen this before.

21
00:06:13,956 --> 00:06:16,125
How did Uma Thurman get out of here again?

22
00:06:17,543 --> 00:06:18,586
What is this?

23
00:06:28,346 --> 00:06:29,430
Ouch!

24
00:06:30,807 --> 00:06:31,974
I can't breathe anymore!

25
00:07:09,011 --> 00:07:11,431
Smoky air and polluted particles?

26
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:12,890
I'm back in the Philippines.

27
00:07:13,933 --> 00:07:16,352
Wait, what happened?

28
00:07:17,770 --> 00:07:20,273
Can you at least debrief me first?

29
00:07:21,983 --> 00:07:23,443
Well, believe it or not,

30
00:07:23,526 --> 00:07:26,446
it was easier to transport
the two of you in coffins.

31
00:07:28,573 --> 00:07:31,367
Sweetheart, you too?
They put you in a coffin too?

32
00:07:33,369 --> 00:07:36,372
But unlike you,
I wasn't being overly dramatic.

33
00:07:38,207 --> 00:07:40,710
Fine, you're the cool, calm,
and collected one.

34
00:07:40,793 --> 00:07:42,837
I'm the one who's always over the top.

35
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,715
It's called emotion regulation.

36
00:07:46,674 --> 00:07:50,219
Don't worry, we have protocols
for situations like this at the agency.

37
00:07:50,303 --> 00:07:52,763
We're actually allowed to use coffins.

38
00:07:52,847 --> 00:07:55,266
And I also gave both of you
strong sedatives,

39
00:07:55,349 --> 00:07:57,685
so you wouldn't get claustrophobic
during the trip.

40
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:02,190
Thanks for those strong sedatives
you gave us.

41
00:08:02,690 --> 00:08:04,650
I don't even know what's going on anymore.

42
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:12,158
This.

43
00:08:14,327 --> 00:08:16,954
Since you still haven't signed
the immunity agreement,

44
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:19,874
you are still considered
enemies of the law.

45
00:08:20,458 --> 00:08:21,918
So you need to wear those.

46
00:08:25,421 --> 00:08:27,507
I remember these!

47
00:08:27,590 --> 00:08:30,635
They're just like the wedding booths
during school intramurals, right?

48
00:08:31,219 --> 00:08:32,929
Sweetheart, this was
how it worked back then.

49
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:35,431
If you had a crush at school,
you'd handcuff them,

50
00:08:35,515 --> 00:08:37,642
then you'd both go into the wedding booth.

51
00:08:37,725 --> 00:08:39,143
You know what that means.

52
00:08:39,727 --> 00:08:43,356
- So you've been married before?
- No.

53
00:08:44,065 --> 00:08:47,318
Come on, sweetheart, it was just for fun,
and I was still a kid back then.

54
00:08:48,361 --> 00:08:49,904
Little Mikoy?

55
00:08:53,658 --> 00:08:54,700
Very little.

56
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:58,829
Chiara, please put it on.

57
00:09:33,614 --> 00:09:35,116
Come back again, okay?

58
00:09:35,199 --> 00:09:36,450
Tess!

59
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:37,535
- What?
- Tess!

60
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:38,953
- Uncle Pepe.
- You have a visitor.

61
00:09:39,036 --> 00:09:40,079
Who?

62
00:09:40,162 --> 00:09:41,122
That one.

63
00:09:45,167 --> 00:09:48,337
Sofie, come here! What brings you here?

64
00:09:48,838 --> 00:09:50,131
I'm applying for a job.

65
00:09:50,214 --> 00:09:51,340
Oh, dear.

66
00:09:51,424 --> 00:09:54,176
Are you really sure about this, child?

67
00:09:54,260 --> 00:09:57,138
You know this will ruin
your summer vacation.

68
00:09:57,680 --> 00:10:01,100
I'm absolutely sure,
and Daddy already approved it.

69
00:10:02,727 --> 00:10:06,397
Okay. Let me just manage
your expectations first, okay?

70
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:08,399
Just look at our bakery.

71
00:10:08,482 --> 00:10:10,943
It's very small and not high-tech.

72
00:10:11,027 --> 00:10:12,945
And look at our oven.

73
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:16,490
Right, Betchay and Angel?

74
00:10:16,574 --> 00:10:19,285
We're always drenched in sweat here.

75
00:10:19,368 --> 00:10:21,203
Are you even used to working in the heat?

76
00:10:21,287 --> 00:10:23,831
Your skin will get all sticky
from the heat around here.

77
00:10:23,914 --> 00:10:26,417
And during summer vacation,

78
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:28,419
there are fiestas one after another
in the barangays.

79
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,506
I'm telling you, you won't get any rest.

80
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:34,759
- You won't even have time to sit down.
- True.

81
00:10:37,553 --> 00:10:39,722
Wow. Okay.

82
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:42,350
I'm not trying
to discourage you, okay, Sofie?

83
00:10:42,433 --> 00:10:44,852
But are you really sure
this is what you want?

84
00:10:45,436 --> 00:10:47,480
Yes, I'm absolutely sure.

85
00:10:47,563 --> 00:10:49,357
I don't care about
the heat or the exhaustion,

86
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,360
and no matter how many orders there are,
I can handle it.

87
00:10:52,443 --> 00:10:54,362
Because a summer job
is exactly what I'm looking for.

88
00:10:54,445 --> 00:10:56,656
Besides, there's no such thing
as an easy job.

89
00:10:56,739 --> 00:10:59,408
My goal is to develop life skills

90
00:10:59,492 --> 00:11:02,078
that I can't easily learn in school.

91
00:11:02,161 --> 00:11:06,082
Well then, why don't you look
for a different summer job?

92
00:11:06,165 --> 00:11:07,249
Right?

93
00:11:07,333 --> 00:11:10,044
One that aligns with those life skills.
Why work here with us?

94
00:11:10,127 --> 00:11:11,170
Good point.

95
00:11:11,253 --> 00:11:12,880
Because I want to work here!

96
00:11:12,963 --> 00:11:15,591
And I also want to spend time
with Mama Tess.

97
00:11:16,425 --> 00:11:18,803
Really! You're flattering me now.

98
00:11:18,886 --> 00:11:20,638
Oh, no, I'm not flattering you.

99
00:11:20,721 --> 00:11:24,016
You know, I've always wanted
to learn how to bake.

100
00:11:24,100 --> 00:11:26,102
And now I finally have the chance.

101
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:28,979
And the best part is,
we'll get to bond too.

102
00:11:29,730 --> 00:11:32,942
That way, it's like getting
to know my mom better too.

103
00:11:35,694 --> 00:11:37,363
You really are something, kid.

104
00:11:37,446 --> 00:11:40,157
You really will do anything, won't you,
to get what you want.

105
00:11:40,241 --> 00:11:42,118
Tell me about it.

106
00:11:42,201 --> 00:11:44,995
You can never beat Sofie's determination.

107
00:11:53,170 --> 00:11:55,881
All right, hija!
You're officially a baker now!

108
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,341
Oh, my baker!

109
00:11:57,425 --> 00:12:00,052
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL BAKESHOP

110
00:12:01,178 --> 00:12:02,596
Where are we?

111
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:08,811
And it's part of the immunity agreement
you're about to sign.

112
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:13,941
And just how safe is this safe house?

113
00:12:15,734 --> 00:12:18,279
Well, it's very safe here.

114
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:20,364
And it's just the two of you--

115
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:39,842
Surprised?

116
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:44,096
Don't worry. It's just us.

117
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:58,277
We're also joined by Senator Quintin,

118
00:12:58,360 --> 00:12:59,862
who has been helping us with this case.

119
00:13:00,529 --> 00:13:02,698
Senator Quintin, winning as always.

120
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:11,874
Oh.

121
00:13:38,484 --> 00:13:39,568
Wow.

122
00:13:39,652 --> 00:13:42,655
This is the first time
I've been starstruck by an assassin.

123
00:13:43,822 --> 00:13:45,491
You're actually cute.

124
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:49,578
And you're handcuffed to your boyfriend.

125
00:13:49,662 --> 00:13:51,413
You two are so cute together.
You make a great pair.

126
00:13:56,252 --> 00:13:59,088
You look like a couple
of tame little kittens.

127
00:14:14,103 --> 00:14:15,312
Now?

128
00:14:17,690 --> 00:14:19,650
Do we still look like tame kittens?

129
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:52,224
We're not underestimating you.

130
00:14:57,313 --> 00:14:59,773
Because we're willing to cooperate.

131
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,445
I hope you are too.

132
00:15:15,915 --> 00:15:17,374
Didn't I tell you?

133
00:15:17,458 --> 00:15:20,252
Lock your holster
so nobody can grab your gun.

134
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:21,503
You're so stubborn.

135
00:15:21,587 --> 00:15:22,755
It's already loose.

136
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:25,633
When we get our bonus, I'll buy a new one.

137
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,761
You just lost beauty points with me.

138
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,014
Turns out you're not respectful.

139
00:15:43,567 --> 00:15:45,611
Take them to the living room first.

140
00:15:46,278 --> 00:15:48,739
Somewhere we can keep an eye on them.

141
00:15:50,032 --> 00:15:53,327
We have to talk about some things first.

142
00:15:54,244 --> 00:15:56,622
Sir. I promise you, sir.

143
00:15:56,705 --> 00:15:58,624
Chiara can help us a lot.

144
00:16:02,795 --> 00:16:05,589
Besides, it's more fun here too.

145
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:08,759
I'm getting tired of dumplings
and Hong Kong fried noodles.

146
00:16:10,636 --> 00:16:11,679
But for now,

147
00:16:12,554 --> 00:16:16,058
leave us for a moment, La Fornarina.

148
00:16:21,605 --> 00:16:22,690
It's simpler.

149
00:16:29,113 --> 00:16:31,532
Let the bosses
have their discussion, okay?

150
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,552
Oh, wow!

151
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:56,557
Well, Angelito's shirt
looks so good on you.

152
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:59,101
Even if it's just a little bit oversized.

153
00:16:59,184 --> 00:17:00,144
Oh.

154
00:17:00,227 --> 00:17:04,273
It's perfectly fine with me.
I don't mind if it's a little big on me.

155
00:17:04,356 --> 00:17:06,150
Besides, this isn't the first time

156
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:08,444
he's let me borrow his things.

157
00:17:12,072 --> 00:17:13,949
Girl, that's not exactly a flex.

158
00:17:15,909 --> 00:17:17,703
That was my spare toothbrush.

159
00:17:17,786 --> 00:17:21,790
Besides, that's in the past.
Let's not bring up the past anymore.

160
00:17:21,874 --> 00:17:23,000
Let's just forget about it.

161
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:25,252
All right, all right, all right.

162
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:27,629
You need to head upstairs
to the kitchen now

163
00:17:27,713 --> 00:17:31,175
because I need to work and prepare lunch!

164
00:17:35,971 --> 00:17:37,056
We have a delivery to make.

165
00:17:37,681 --> 00:17:39,099
Leave that to the kids.

166
00:17:39,183 --> 00:17:41,727
We'll work upstairs. Come on.

167
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:49,026
- Come on, already. Let's work upstairs.
- Oh, yeah.

168
00:17:50,944 --> 00:17:51,987
Good grief!

169
00:17:54,948 --> 00:17:57,659
Look who's talking. You're the one
telling Mom all sorts of things.

170
00:17:57,743 --> 00:17:58,744
So embarrassing.

171
00:17:58,827 --> 00:18:00,704
Embarrassing? Didn't you see that?

172
00:18:00,788 --> 00:18:02,831
Mom was totally fine with it.

173
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,750
So then, where do we start?

174
00:18:04,833 --> 00:18:07,961
You know, it's not too late.
You can still back out.

175
00:18:08,545 --> 00:18:10,297
Just relax at the resort.

176
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:12,633
Look how hot it is.
It's perfect weather for swimming.

177
00:18:12,716 --> 00:18:13,967
You know what?

178
00:18:14,051 --> 00:18:15,552
You're a great pretender.

179
00:18:15,636 --> 00:18:16,970
{\an8}Whenever your parents are around,

180
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:19,973
{\an8}you're so nice, like some kind of angel.

181
00:18:20,057 --> 00:18:22,309
{\an8}But once they're gone, there you go.

182
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:25,354
{\an8}It's like you want to kick me out
of your bakery.

183
00:18:25,437 --> 00:18:26,897
Oh, please.

184
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:28,398
If I'm a great pretender,

185
00:18:28,482 --> 00:18:30,692
then you're a great manipulator!

186
00:18:30,776 --> 00:18:33,612
Look how quickly you got
Mom and Dad to say yes.

187
00:18:33,695 --> 00:18:36,323
Not just this time, but with
so many people in so many situations.

188
00:18:36,406 --> 00:18:38,867
Whenever you want something, you get it.

189
00:18:39,451 --> 00:18:41,495
You're the only thing that's hard to get.

190
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:43,288
- You're so difficult.
- Because

191
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,837
All right, let's get to work.

192
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,881
We still have 100 cakes
to finish and deliver.

193
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:56,051
{\an8}- One hundred? That many?
- Yes.

194
00:18:56,677 --> 00:18:57,761
Can I cut in?

195
00:18:57,845 --> 00:19:01,265
Yes, 100. One hundred. <i>Siento!</i>

196
00:19:01,348 --> 00:19:03,642
So save your little drama
for later, you two!

197
00:19:03,725 --> 00:19:06,186
We need to bake 100 cakes.

198
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:08,438
So help us God. Let's go. Come on.

199
00:19:18,115 --> 00:19:21,243
Looks like I need to schedule
an appointment with my nail tech.

200
00:19:21,952 --> 00:19:23,579
My nails are starting to chip.

201
00:19:25,289 --> 00:19:26,874
I know what that means when you do that.

202
00:19:31,336 --> 00:19:33,714
That you don't want to talk about
what you did earlier.

203
00:19:33,797 --> 00:19:35,799
What did I do?

204
00:19:44,224 --> 00:19:45,434
He started it.

205
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:48,020
And you know I hate it
when people underestimate me.

206
00:19:48,103 --> 00:19:50,606
Even so, sweetheart, he's still a senator.

207
00:19:50,689 --> 00:19:52,357
And even if he weren't a senator,

208
00:19:52,441 --> 00:19:54,651
it would still be wrong
to point a gun at someone.

209
00:19:55,861 --> 00:19:57,321
Come on, sweetheart.

210
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:03,410
What if they have another plan,

211
00:20:03,493 --> 00:20:05,204
and that's why they want immunity?

212
00:20:05,829 --> 00:20:07,206
And what if

213
00:20:07,831 --> 00:20:13,128
they're just making up stories
about having something valuable for us?

214
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,630
You know,

215
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:17,883
it's true that Chiara has a scary stare.

216
00:20:17,966 --> 00:20:19,384
Very intense.

217
00:20:19,885 --> 00:20:23,847
But those are exactly the kinds of girls
who fall for my charm.

218
00:20:25,557 --> 00:20:29,228
Just give me one or two days.

219
00:20:29,311 --> 00:20:31,271
She'll fall for me, I promise.

220
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:34,191
Wow, you're really making promises now?

221
00:20:34,274 --> 00:20:36,735
You know Chiara.
She'd throw you off a cliff.

222
00:20:43,742 --> 00:20:46,370
You need to tone down
your violent tendencies

223
00:20:46,453 --> 00:20:48,497
if you want to make a deal
with the agency.

224
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:52,668
We're here to cooperate,
not to start a shootout.

225
00:20:52,751 --> 00:20:56,213
Well, I have my reasons for doing that.

226
00:20:56,964 --> 00:20:58,048
Go ahead then.

227
00:20:58,131 --> 00:21:00,676
Give me one good reason why you did it.

228
00:21:03,303 --> 00:21:06,390
To show them that even if
we're willing to help,

229
00:21:06,974 --> 00:21:08,684
we remain dangerous,

230
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:10,978
and we're not easily manipulated.

231
00:21:16,525 --> 00:21:18,777
And if they go back on their promise,

232
00:21:18,860 --> 00:21:21,113
I'll take them out one by one.

233
00:21:23,323 --> 00:21:25,659
To be honest, at first,
I didn't believe them either.

234
00:21:30,664 --> 00:21:32,958
I know Chiara has explosive information

235
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:35,294
that could change the course
of this entire story.

236
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:51,810
Looks like she's been blinded
by her love for Mikoy.

237
00:21:52,436 --> 00:21:54,229
She wants immunity because

238
00:21:54,938 --> 00:21:57,774
she wants a future
with the man she loves most.

239
00:23:30,325 --> 00:23:33,203
Whatever information she has,

240
00:23:33,286 --> 00:23:36,081
well, at least we'll be one step ahead

241
00:23:36,164 --> 00:23:38,708
of a bigger and more dangerous enemy

242
00:23:40,001 --> 00:23:41,545
other than the Moravianos.

243
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:38,101
What is this Concordat?

244
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:56,703
That is why the Philippines
is very important to the mafia.

245
00:24:56,786 --> 00:24:59,789
Because in this country lies the weapon

246
00:24:59,873 --> 00:25:03,418
that will bring chaos and instability
to the entire world.

247
00:25:03,501 --> 00:25:05,670
Nobody got this weapon, right?

248
00:25:10,675 --> 00:25:12,427
What is that gut feel?

249
00:25:12,510 --> 00:25:14,638
Because I have a feeling

250
00:25:14,721 --> 00:25:18,558
it was a mistake to leave Ben there
to watch over Mikoy and Chiara.

251
00:25:25,565 --> 00:25:26,858
Mikoy and Chiara are missing.

252
00:25:26,942 --> 00:25:28,151
What?

